 :tx/rationale "Create task: CE-OAR: Observation-Aware Routing — dampen explored areas, boost unexplored. CONTEXT: R(t) routing has zero signal from observation history. After recording 8 observations about the consistency engine, R(t) still recommends 'Review consistency engine' as top task. Guidance responsiveness scored 2.3/10. RATIONALE: Closing the observation->routing loop. Agent's work must feed back into recommendations. APPROACH: (1) In compute_routing_from_store_inner (routing.rs), after computing base routing, add observation-awareness pass. (2) Collect session observations: entities with :exploration/body asserted after last harvest tx. Tokenize each observation's body into keyword sets. (3) For each ready task: tokenize title + :task/body into keyword set. Compute max Jaccard overlap with any session observation. (4) Observation dampening: if max_overlap > 0.15, apply dampening_factor = 0.3 * (1.0 - max_overlap). Tasks heavily covered by observations sink. (5) Unexplored boost: count how many task namespaces (extracted from :task/traces-to refs) have NO session observations. Tasks in un-observed namespaces get 1.5x boost. (6) The effect: as the agent works in area X, tasks about X are dampened and tasks about unexplored areas Y, Z rise. Guidance naturally rotates attention to unexplored territory. (7) This feeds the annealing: explored areas have lower free energy (dampened), unexplored areas have higher free energy (boosted). The routing gradient points away from known territory toward unknown territory. ACCEPTANCE: (A) After 3 observations about 'consistency engine', task t-bbdb5756 'Review consistency engine' drops from top-3. (B) Tasks in un-observed namespaces rise in ranking. (C) With zero observations, routing is unchanged (no regression). (D) M(t) status line reflects observation-based dampening activity. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/routing.rs (compute_routing_from_store_inner)"
